<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.SSMN96.S80"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[423,000] s 80 How does an owners corporation recover unpaid contributions and interest?">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.SSMN96.S80" type="ext"/>[423,000]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">How does an owners corporation recover unpaid contributions and interest?</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>80</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.SSMN96.S80.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.SSMN96.S80.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>An owners corporation may recover as a debt a contribution not paid at the end of one month after it becomes due and payable, together with any interest payable and the expenses of the owners corporation incurred in recovering those amounts.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.SSMN96.S80.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.SSMN96.S80.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Interest paid or recovered forms part of the fund to which the relevant contribution belongs.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.OL.SSMN96.S80.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.SSMN96.423000-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[423,000.5] Expenses">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [423,000.5] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text> </text>
<text>(NSW) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005Y" refpt="NSW_ACT_2007-93" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Local Court Act 2007</remotelink> s 37.</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.SSMN96.423000-5" type="ext"/>[423,000.5] </edpnum><title>Expenses</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The word &#x201c;expenses&#x201d; in s 80 does include legal costs and disbursements: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000504" spanref="cr000504-001"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC200900947"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000504" spanref="cr000504-002"><ci:pinpoint num="33" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Owners of Strata Plan 36131 v Dimitriou</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> [2009] NSWCA 27; <ci:span spanid="cr000504-001"> BC200900947</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000504-002">at [33]</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="470149" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> per Hodgson JA, <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000505" spanref="cr000505-000"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:pinpoint num="62" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"><ci:span spanid="cr000505-000">at [62]</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> per Basten JA, <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000506" spanref="cr000506-000"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:pinpoint num="116" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"><ci:span spanid="cr000506-000">at [116]</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> per Handley AJA. Section 80(1) confers a right on a corporation to recover legal costs, reasonably incurred and reasonable in amount, as expenses as a component of the principal judgment of the court, independently of any costs orders that may or may not be made in those proceedings: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000507" spanref="cr000507-000"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:pinpoint num="34" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"><ci:span spanid="cr000507-000">at [34]&#x2013;[36]</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> per Hodgson JA; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000508" spanref="cr000508-000"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:pinpoint num="127" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"><ci:span spanid="cr000508-000">at [127]</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> per Handley AJA; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000509" spanref="cr000509-000"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:pinpoint num="102" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"><ci:span spanid="cr000509-000">at [102]</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> per Basten JA contra.</text></p>
<p>
<text>The words &#x201c;together with&#x201d; in s 80 mean that the claim for expenses, including legal costs and disbursements, must be made in the same proceedings as the claim for the contributions. The payment of arrears of contributions before proceedings are commenced will preclude an action for recovery of associated expenses. However, payment of arrears of contributions after proceedings have been commenced will not preclude continuation of those proceedings to obtain a judgment for expenses including legal costs: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000510" spanref="cr000510-000"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:pinpoint num="47" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"><ci:span spanid="cr000510-000">at [47]</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> per Hodgson JA; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000511" spanref="cr000511-000"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:pinpoint num="142" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"><ci:span spanid="cr000511-000">at [142]</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> per Handley AJA; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000512" spanref="cr000512-000"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:pinpoint num="106" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"><ci:span spanid="cr000512-000">at [106]</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> per Basten JA contra.</text></p>
<p>
<text>The legal costs incurred in proceedings before the Strata Schemes Adjudicator or the Consumer and Tenancy Tribunal are recoverable, if the costs are truly to be characterised as having been incurred in recovering arrears of contributions: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000513" spanref="cr000513-000"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:pinpoint num="43" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"><ci:span spanid="cr000513-000">at [43]</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> per Hodgson JA, Handley AJA agreeing, Basten JA dissenting. Notwithstanding Local Court Act 2007 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.LC.LCAN07.S37" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">s 37</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 (which provides that the Local Court sitting in its Small Claims Division has no power to award costs), the Court of Appeal&#x2019;s decision in <emph typestyle="it">Dimitriou</emph>, is authority for the proposition that the Small Claims Division of the Local Court does not lack jurisdiction to determine an owners corporation&#x2019;s claim under Strata Schemes Management Act 1996 s 80 for its legal costs incurred in recovering unpaid contributions: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000514" spanref="cr000514-001" status="unval"><ci:volume num=""/><ci:page num=""/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000515" spanref="cr000515-002"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC200902727"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">McClymont v The Owners-Strata Plan No 1</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000514-001" status="unval">2139 [2009] NSWSC 276</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000515-002"> BC200902727</ci:span> at [29]</citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="472496" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> per McCallum J. The section confers on an owners corporation a right of action enabling the recovery of contributions and any interest payable. Any claim for contributions and expenses must be litigated at one and the same time, in the same action: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000516" spanref="cr000516-001"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC200701662"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Owners of Strata Plan 53800 v Wolfe </emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> [2007] NSWSC 204; <ci:span spanid="cr000516-001"> BC200701662</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="434271" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> per Malpass AsJ, noted in <emph typestyle="it">Dimitriou</emph> <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000517" spanref="cr000517-000"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:pinpoint num="26" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"><ci:span spanid="cr000517-000">at [26]</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>.</text></p>
</bodytext>
